ction-dependent frequency tuning was effectively abolished by occlusion of the ipsilateral ear. Possible mechanisms underlying these observations are discussed.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Lu, Yong", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jen, Philip H.-S", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/770ae2c3d2c5e2915d18c6d96b476022", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/0d6877278f2cb5b0f9a74995c6bf2f7edc3b43d8a4515d7da616b893b7ebdab1", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/M6LIZ3BH", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/M6LIZ3BH", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/9a5757cabdd6626f3f53e83cff62ae3a!/b56898-59352", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1-2", "pages": "100-110", "title": "Hearing Research", "volume": "177"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/770ae2c3d2c5e2915d18c6d96b476022"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:M6LIZ3BH"}, {"identifier": "10.1016/S0378-5955(03)00024-8"}], "communities": [{"id": "batlit"}, {"id": "biosyslit"}], "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_last": true, "parent": {"pid_type": "recid", "pid_value": "13451244"}}]}}, "title": "Binaural interaction in the inferior 